Package: tennispreds
Title: ATP Men's Tennis Match-Outcome Predictor
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: person("Mona", "Ascha", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Internal project (not a distributed package): the
    Tennis_Data_Prep pipeline carved into R/ pure functions plus a
    Plumber prediction API. This DESCRIPTION is the renv dependency
    manifest. Imports = the lean runtime set used by R/ and api.R
    (dplyr..xgboost) PLUS the training-time modelling stack
    (parsnip/workflows/yardstick/rsample) used by analysis/ scripts;
    they share Imports because renv's explicit snapshot treats
    Suggests as dev-only and would not lock them. The API itself never
    needs the modelling packages -- it serves a saved model. The
    legacy markdowns/ ML stack (keras, tidymodels meta, caret, ...) is
    intentionally NOT locked: those notebooks are retired/migrated in
    refactor step 5. Re-snapshot after modelling deps grow (e.g. tune/
    dials when hyperparameter tuning lands).
Encoding: UTF-8
Imports:
    dplyr,
    tidyr,
    naniar,
    stringr,
    lubridate,
    runner,
    fastDummies,
    here,
    plumber,
    xgboost,
